	   <tr><td colspan=2>From what training I've recieved, the movements of a Sai are almost purely for defense or for blunt striking; we have no piercing movements with our sais in Ishinryu karate, which is a combination of goginryu (Okinawa) and shorinryu (mainland eastern Asia, around China I believe). However, many trapping movements and strikes are done, but never are they used to pierce. And whoever said that they have no weight has obviously have no experience with them. Dropping them on your foot is very painful. I think this is a great representation of a sai from RL; it's a rather fast weapon, and the AC bonus shows their original defensive purposes. except, of course, for the lore part, since our katas use 3 sais :). Oh well, can't have everything :)<br>&nbsp;<br>Hasame<br><br>"He who becomes like the beast gets over the pain of being a man."</td></tr>
